    <section id="team" class="panel" data-delay="160">
      <div class="panel-content">
        <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
          <SectionHeading title="Our team" lead="Meet the team who's creating your deorbiting solution." />
          <div class="mt-10 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-5">
            {team.map(m => (
              <div class="card p-4 text-center" role="group" aria-label={`${m.name}, ${m.role}`}>
                <img
                  src={m.img}
                  alt={`${m.name} portrait`}
                  class="mx-auto h-24 w-24 rounded-full object-cover"
                  loading="lazy"
                  decoding="async"
                />
                <h4 class="mt-3 font-semibold">{m.name}</h4>
                <p class="text-white/70 text-sm">{m.role}</p>
                <div class="mt-3 flex items-center justify-center gap-2">
                  <!-- TODO: remove these comments -->
                  <!-- <a href={m.links.linkedin} class="nav-link">LinkedIn</a> -->
                  <!-- <a href={m.links.github} class="nav-link">GitHub</a> -->
                </div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="heritage" class="panel" data-delay="260" data-slide="10px">
      <div class="panel-content">
        <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
          <SectionHeading title="Heritage" lead="ASDS Space Technologies spun out of Project TELLER to create deployable dragsail systems." />
          <div class="mt-10 grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="card p-6 space-y-4">
              <p class="text-white/80">
               <a href="https://teller.bme.hu" class="text-blue-600 visited:text-purple-600 hover:underline">Project TELLER</a> (Three-axis Experimental Low-altitude Laboratory for Exploring Radiation) is a Hungarian student team in the ESA/DLR REXUS/BEXUS programme, which flies up to twenty university-built experiments on sounding rockets and balloons each year.
              </p>
              <p class="text-white/80">
              Working inside that framework taught us how to qualify hardware for rocket launches, how to design resilient and robust systems, all fundamentals that now reside inside the company.
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/80 space-y-1 space-bullets">
                <li>Hands-on experience with sounding rocket payload design bound for ~90 km apogee.</li>
                <li>Close collaboration with ESA, SSC, DLR, and mentors on safety reviews.</li>
                <li>Experience with ECSS standards, harsh environmental requirements and tight deadlines.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="card p-6 space-y-4">
              <p class="text-white/80">
              Several founding members come from <a href="https://suborbitals.bme.hu/en/" class="text-blue-600 visited:text-purple-600 hover:underline">BME Suborbitals</a>, carrying forward their structural, avionics, and campaign logistics know-how into ASDS Space Technologies.
              </p>
              <p class="text-white/80">
                The combination of Project TELLER flight heritage and BME Suborbitals systems engineering lets us deliver a turnkey, tuna-can sized deorbit module with the rigor of institutional missions but the cadence of a startup.
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/80 space-y-1 space-bullets">
                <li>Shared checklists and GSE concepts from sounding rocket flight campaigns.</li>
                <li>We can easily carry over previous experience working with sounding rockets.</li>
                <li>A cross-trained crew that has already passed ESA-level design reviews together.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="contact" class="panel" data-slide="10px">
      <div class="panel-content">
        <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
          <SectionHeading title="Get in touch" lead="Need integration support or compliance data?" />
          <div class="mt-10 card p-6">
              <p class="text-white/80">Email us at <a class="nav-link bg-clip-text text-transparent bg-gradient-to-r from-neon-cyan via-neon-blue to-neon-purple" href="mailto:info@asds.tech">info@asds.tech</a> for data sheets, CAD models, and pricing.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
